Label: Credit By Exam
Definition: Credit granted from successful score on a standardized test of comprehension or proficiency.

Label: High School Transfer Credit
Definition: Credit from a high school course is transferred to the college.

Label: High School Credit Only
Definition: Credit from a college course is transferred back to high school and not counted by the college.

Label: High School Dual Credit
Definition: Credit from a college course is counted at both the college and high school.

Label: Junior High School Credit
Definition: Credit from a junior high school course is counted at the high school.

Label: Major
Definition: Credit associated with the student's major AcademicRenewal AdultBasic AdvancedPlacement AdvancedStanding Correspondence ContinuingEducation Exemption Equivalence InternationalBaccalaureate Military

Label: Credit Basis
Definition: The type of enrollment associated with the credit hours for the course.
